## [Date: 2025-12-21] - Initial Creation

### Created
- Skill created via creating-skills workflow
- RED failure documented: Threat modeling orchestrator jumps directly to Phase 1 codebase mapping without sizing assessment, causing agent timeouts and inefficient parallelization
- Category: skill-library/security
- Type: process/pattern (methodology)

### Purpose
- Assess codebase size before threat modeling Phase 1
- Count files per component, categorize as small/medium/large
- Output sizing-report.json with parallelization strategy
- Inform codebase-mapper agent spawn decisions

### Initial Content
- 5-step workflow (file counting, component discovery, categorization, security scoring, strategy recommendation)
- Strategy matrix with small/medium/large tiers
- JSON output schema for orchestrator consumption
- Integration guidance for threat-modeling-orchestrator
